  {
   "type": "para",
   "marker": "ip",
   "content": [
    "This document records some of GodвҖҷs messages that were given to the prophet Malaki (more accurately вҖҳMalКјДҒkД«вҖҷ, although traditionally spelt as вҖҳMalachiвҖҷ) to pass on to the Israeli people. It was written around 500 years before Yeshua/Jesus (B.C.) once the replacement temple was finished in Yerushalem (Jerusalem). The main purpose of the messages is to encourage the priests and the people to turn back to God and obey him from their hearts. ItвҖҷs apparent that many of them were no longer obeying and worshipping God. The priests and the people were short-changing God by offering second-class animals for the sacrifices and none of them were following GodвҖҷs desires. But God intervened in order to judge and restore his people, and he will send a teacher to precede him to prepare the path and to restore his agreement.\n"
   ]
